{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567143","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567143"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:55:40+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:55:40+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18938"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18938","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18938"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.9,0.01,0.02,0.05,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11672"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"112697"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11672","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11672"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18938"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94730"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"928"},{"type":"tags","id":"3798"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5752"},{"type":"tags","id":"5770"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11282"},{"type":"tags","id":"11304"},{"type":"tags","id":"11310"},{"type":"tags","id":"11380"},{"type":"tags","id":"11398"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27465"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27480"},{"type":"contributions","id":"46231"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"112697","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/112697"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA medical student observes a junior doctor prescribing antibiotics for a patient with clear viral upper respiratory tract symptoms. The student has recently attended a lecture on antimicrobial stewardship and believes the prescription is inappropriate.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate professional response from the medical student?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Discuss concerns privately with the junior doctor after the consultation","Inform the patient that antibiotics are not needed for viral infections","Submit anonymous feedback to the clinic manager","Report the incident directly to the consultant","Immediately correct the junior doctor in front of the patient"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most appropriate response is to \u003Cstrong\u003Ediscuss concerns privately with the junior doctor after the consultation\u003C/strong\u003E. This approach maintains professional relationships, allows for educational dialogue, and addresses the concern while respecting both parties.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options are inappropriate because:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImmediately correct the junior doctor in front of the patient\u003C/strong\u003E - This undermines the doctor-patient relationship and is unprofessional\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReport the incident directly to the consultant\u003C/strong\u003E - This bypasses appropriate channels of communication and may damage professional relationships unnecessarily\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESubmit anonymous feedback to the clinic manager\u003C/strong\u003E - Anonymous complaints bypass direct communication and may create an environment of distrust\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInform the patient that antibiotics are not needed for viral infections\u003C/strong\u003E - This undermines the treating doctor\u0027s authority and may confuse the patient, potentially damaging the therapeutic relationship\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EProfessional disagreements should be handled with respect, in private, and with a focus on patient care and learning opportunities. This maintains positive working relationships while ensuring patient safety remains the priority.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Professional disagreements in healthcare should be discussed privately, not in front of patients or other staff.","Medical students should respect the clinical hierarchy while still advocating for patient safety.","Constructive feedback should focus on specific concerns rather than personal criticism."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94730"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18938"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94730","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/94730"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-04T08:18:46+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-04T08:19:44+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11672"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"112697"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"